In some half-waking swoon, bewilder'd, lay she,
Until the poppy-warmth of sleep suppress'd
Her lull'd-out limbs, and wearied soul did flee;
Gone, like a thought, unto the morrow’s lee;
Blissfully harbored both from joy and pain;
